Hungarian legislation distinguishes between national holidays and state holidays as well as days of rest.
Rest days are often linked to religious celebrations or important historical events.
In Hungary, we celebrate the new year, the last day of the year that ends and the first day of the new year are also days of rest, especially so that the wake-up workers can rest quietly.
Furthermore, in a year we have eleven holidays marked in red.
March 15 is a national holiday, in commemoration of the revolution of 1848, as on October 23, also which is the commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20, we celebrate the constitution of our state, on May 1st is the holiday of work, and on November 1 and 2, we remember members of our deceased family and friends.
In addition, we have two days in Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
The days of our state, national or religious holidays rarely falling on a weekend, according to the schedule, it has become common to reorganize working days in cases where there is only one working day before or after the holiday marked in red.
