Congress approves the transposition of MiFID, which entered into force on 1 November.
In parallel to its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the Congress's vote on amendments incorporated into the draft in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the rules that will develop the new law, with the aim of its entry into force before the year ends.
The representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the efforts made by Members of Parliament and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulation that would guarantee investor protection and to regulate the activities of organizations in detail so that markets would function effectively.
The Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, involves the modernisation of financial markets, at the time when it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the leaders of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the various leaders of the European Union.
