What kind of insurance do I need?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of potential claims, entails a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, gender, seniority of driving licence, civil status, type of vehicle to be insured or the actual use, among others.
Having a car is the most important.
There are, escoger el seguro de automóvil adecuado es inclusiveo más difícil que elegir el modelo de vehículo.
And it's that choosing the proper auto insurance is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in exchange becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a disaster.
The premium is the cost of insurance, which is calculated taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of driving licence, civil status, type of vehicle to be insured or actual use, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rating to be paid.
This is why people over 25 years of age and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that they have lower claims from their caution.
Similarly, using censuses, the companies concluded that married persons tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probability increases.
They are many of the variables that insurers consider when setting the premium price.
That's why the driver has to study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best fits his/her profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when selecting one or the other type of insurance, so that the insurance company, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under 25 years of age must face various disadvantages when entering into a contract with insurance at an affordable price, as may be the lack of experience in driving and the seniority of driving licences.
While the ideal for being well insured is insurance at all risk, other more economical options exist.
The most predictable drivers can opt for all-risk insurance with no charge, so that they get the coverage of all-risk insurance but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the client pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the client pays will be based on the value of the premium, which will be higher than the amount will be lower," explains Luis Noguera, the head in charge of First Europa Spain, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but for those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under 25 years of age trying to be careful and avoid claims as far as possible, since this will impact on the rebate, which may reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A discount is a reduction in the company's basic rate.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic rate.
"The rewards and sanctions will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses," said Noguera.
Over the age of 25, it becomes easier for drivers to enter into a contract with insurance, since the loss rate is reduced due to accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is best to choose any risk insurance with franchise.
"Normally young people cannot take advantage of the experience acquired after an accident", says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to negotiate insurance at any risk, as long as his or her economic situation allows him or her.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be persons with the lowest claims rate, because the increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be an insurance at all risk without charge (may be 300 euros), or a third-party insurance extended from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of credit.
"They have a more casual conduct and they have a greater purchasing power to afford themselves the luxury to assume a greater amount of franchisees," said Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, a risk-free insurance is preferable (by being EUR 150), or an extended third-party insurance where the insurer has a high level of credit.
It must be said that motor insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of potential claims, but also because it represents a significant expense, it is therefore essential to properly study the insurance that is most appropriate to us according to our personal situation.
